 "segments": [
  {
   "start": 0.0,
   "end": 5.22,
   "text": "In China, 5-2-0 means I love you, but 2-5-0 means you idiot."
  },
  {
   "start": 5.9,
   "end": 8.38,
   "text": "Numbers there aren't just numbers, they're a whole secret language."
  },
  {
   "start": 8.84,
   "end": 9.64,
   "text": "Here's how to read it."
  },
  {
   "start": 9.82,
   "end": 13.32,
   "text": "It works because Chinese is full of words that sound almost exactly like numbers."
  },
  {
   "start": 13.78,
   "end": 17.98,
   "text": "So people started using strings of numbers as code, something you can text, comment, or"
  },
  {
   "start": 17.98,
   "end": 18.82,
   "text": "even put on a gift."
  },
  {
   "start": 19.32,
   "end": 21.1,
   "text": "A few digits standing in for a whole phrase."
  },
  {
   "start": 21.64,
   "end": 26.98,
   "text": "Say 5, 2-0 fast, wu air ling, and it sounds like wu ai ni, I love you."
  },
  {
   "start": 26.98,
   "end": 31.3,
   "text": "It's so well known that May 20th it were written 5-20 has become an unofficial romance"
  },
  {
   "start": 31.3,
   "end": 33.0,
   "text": "date like a second valentine's."
  },
  {
   "start": 33.3,
   "end": 40.06,
   "text": "Add 1-3-1-4, which sounds like forever a lifetime, and 5-2-0-1-3-1-4 means I love you forever."
  },
  {
   "start": 40.54,
   "end": 42.04,
   "text": "But the same trick cuts the other way."
  },
  {
   "start": 42.62,
   "end": 46.2,
   "text": "Call someone a 2-5-0, air by wu, and you've called them a fool."
  },
  {
   "start": 46.7,
   "end": 50.82,
   "text": "The story goes it comes from an old expression about half a string of coins, being not quite"
  },
  {
   "start": 50.82,
   "end": 51.3,
   "text": "all there."
  },
  {
   "start": 51.92,
   "end": 52.46,
   "text": "And there's more."
  },
  {
   "start": 52.86,
   "end": 54.32,
   "text": "8-8 sounds like bye bye."
  },
  {
   "start": 54.32,
   "end": 57.8,
   "text": "6-6-6 means you're a legend, seriously skilled."
  },
  {
   "start": 58.4,
   "end": 62.7,
   "text": "A few digits can carry an entire mood, so a string of numbers in a chinese chat might be"
  },
  {
   "start": 62.7,
   "end": 66.0,
   "text": "a maths problem, or a love letter, or an insult."
  },
  {
   "start": 66.54,
   "end": 69.16,
   "text": "One block of numbers, two completely different worlds."
  },
  {
   "start": 69.72,
   "end": 71.0,
   "text": "Want to actually start learning chinese?"
  },
  {
   "start": 71.6,
   "end": 75.9,
   "text": "Discover thousands of free exercises and more learning content on stacktags.io"
  }
 ]
